1
00:00:05,462 --> 00:00:08,404
Hello, this is the talk honoring the blade,

2
00:00:08,404 --> 00:00:11,145
lethality and combat balance in Ghost of Tsushima.

3
00:00:11,145 --> 00:00:15,047
This talk is going to talk a lot about how the Samurai fantasy impacted

4
00:00:15,047 --> 00:00:18,649
our design decisions and our combat balance throughout the game.

5
00:00:18,649 --> 00:00:22,351
But before we go into that, talk a little bit about myself.

6
00:00:22,351 --> 00:00:23,752
My name is Theodore Fishman. I go by Ted.

7
00:00:23,752 --> 00:00:26,893
I've been at Sucker Punch for 11 years.

8
00:00:26,893 --> 00:00:30,055
I'm the lead combat designer there, and I've worked on systems

9
00:00:30,055 --> 00:00:31,716
and combat design all the way through.

10
00:00:31,716 --> 00:00:34,677
And of course, mostly on combat design on Ghost of Tsushima.

11
00:00:36,035 --> 00:00:39,016
So before we get into the actual core design issues we ran into,

12
00:00:39,016 --> 00:00:42,718
it's important to talk about the samurai fantasy.

13
00:00:42,718 --> 00:00:46,339
Flash of steel, few quick strikes and the enemy is dead.

14
00:00:46,339 --> 00:00:48,240
That is the fantasy of a samurai.

15
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:53,742
This is a trope instilled via samurai films, manga, anime, you name it.

16
00:00:53,742 --> 00:00:55,223
We had to fulfill this trope.

17
00:00:55,223 --> 00:00:58,244
But how does that translate into gameplay?

18
00:00:58,244 --> 00:01:01,765
How do you balance a combat for a grounded game,

19
00:01:01,765 --> 00:01:05,427
especially with character and player progression throughout the game?

20
00:01:05,958 --> 00:01:10,341
where you can't have everything die too fast, but still feel lethal?

21
00:01:10,341 --> 00:01:12,483
That is the core we needed to succeed at.

22
00:01:12,483 --> 00:01:14,785
And we had features like standoffs,

23
00:01:14,785 --> 00:01:19,268
and nailed that feeling of lethality and honoring that trope and fantasy.

24
00:01:19,268 --> 00:01:24,372
But how combat is initiated was the main purpose of standoffs.

25
00:01:24,372 --> 00:01:27,174
That didn't really go into the standard combat loop.

26
00:01:27,174 --> 00:01:30,757
How do we bring this feeling of standoffs and match those expectations?

27
00:01:30,757 --> 00:01:33,098
How do we honor the blade feeling lethal and sharp?

28
00:01:36,502 --> 00:01:38,924
So let's kind of break down the core design problem.

29
00:01:38,924 --> 00:01:46,111
We wanted satisfying player progression that included armor, charms, weapons, you name it.

30
00:01:46,111 --> 00:01:49,214
And that had to be for 30 hours of gameplay.

31
00:01:49,214 --> 00:01:52,477
For an open world game, players could go wherever they wanted,

32
00:01:52,477 --> 00:01:55,700
they could go, you know, do content, whatever they wanted to.

33
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:57,682
So we need to have that be satisfying.

34
00:01:57,682 --> 00:01:57,742
And

35
00:01:58,315 --> 00:02:03,937
We had multiple difficulty modes, whether it be easy to hard and later lethal, which we added.

36
00:02:03,937 --> 00:02:08,400
We also had to support a 2-4 player co-op mode for Bronze and up to Raid tier difficulties.

37
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:18,985
Plus, we had a variety of enemies to keep players interested and escalate challenge and difficulty throughout those enemies and feel it through the progression of the game.

38
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:25,101
And we're also an action game, you know, it has to feel fast paced, it has to be responsive,

39
00:02:25,101 --> 00:02:27,501
you know, how do we get players to understand what's happening and read,

40
00:02:27,501 --> 00:02:31,343
you know, like, oh, that felt meaningful, that felt like there was an impact on my decisions

41
00:02:31,343 --> 00:02:36,224
and the choices I made for my builds, my armor, whatever it may be.

42
00:02:36,224 --> 00:02:40,946
But the whole risk that's part of this is that things start to feel like sword sponges,

43
00:02:40,946 --> 00:02:45,067
that HP inflation could, you know, spiral out of control.

44
00:02:45,450 --> 00:02:50,791
specifically because of like, oh, I need to challenge a player and then this sword upgrade doesn't feel meaningful.

45
00:02:50,791 --> 00:02:52,011
That could be a huge issue.

46
00:02:52,011 --> 00:02:54,972
And this is one of the major issues we had to try to, you know, tackle.

47
00:02:54,972 --> 00:02:59,413
So we had to escalate those challenges, we tried things, right?

48
00:02:59,413 --> 00:03:02,494
So the first one was like, you know, standard RPG leveling, right?

49
00:03:02,494 --> 00:03:08,795
Level differences, scale damage and damage to the player, damage to the enemy.

50
00:03:08,795 --> 00:03:13,137
And also, you know, we showed health bars and show how the big difference of each sword strike didn't matter.

51
00:03:13,885 --> 00:03:18,509
But this started to feel really gamey and frayed at the kind of realistic and grounded nature of our game.

52
00:03:18,509 --> 00:03:22,493
And it also felt like your sword wasn't sharp.

53
00:03:22,493 --> 00:03:31,821
And it only got kind of worse when we did the extreme case, you know, other RPGs do this, where you have skulls to show the difference between high and low hero to enemy levels.

54
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:37,264
It felt very artificial and we need to escalate in a different way.

55
00:03:37,264 --> 00:03:40,287
What was even worse was that you can do this in an open world scenario

56
00:03:40,287 --> 00:03:43,249
pretty easily if you just kind of travel outside the boundaries.

57
00:03:43,249 --> 00:03:45,592
Originally, this was what we're looking for.

58
00:03:45,592 --> 00:03:48,234
We're like, you know, you should do this mission and upgrade your armor

59
00:03:48,234 --> 00:03:49,695
and your sword.

60
00:03:49,695 --> 00:03:52,077
But this became kind of harmful to the fantasy.

61
00:03:52,077 --> 00:03:52,538
And we've tried to go.

62
00:03:59,187 --> 00:04:04,954
it, maybe literally, where we had a shield of HP around the like a low health of a

63
00:04:04,954 --> 00:04:09,199
red health bar. So in this video we talk a little bit, show here a little bit

64
00:04:09,199 --> 00:04:13,444
about like hey this orange barrier around the red health points keep them

65
00:04:13,444 --> 00:04:16,768
like you know three to four hits to kill the guy but if you could break through

66
00:04:16,768 --> 00:04:17,329
the shield.

67
00:04:18,050 --> 00:04:21,672
We had weapon scaling and like to go through, you know, armor faster,

68
00:04:21,672 --> 00:04:24,773
but it was really opaque and people had a hard time understanding

69
00:04:24,773 --> 00:04:26,073
what was going on there.

70
00:04:26,073 --> 00:04:28,854
And plus, even though it was done in other games, which is, you know,

71
00:04:28,854 --> 00:04:30,374
a totally fine way to approach it,

72
00:04:30,374 --> 00:04:34,156
it didn't feel like lethal or matching the fantasy we wanted for the samurai game.

73
00:04:34,156 --> 00:04:38,677
So we tried it on multiple different things,

74
00:04:38,677 --> 00:04:41,978
we did a lot of internal and external testing, and we wanted to see

75
00:04:41,978 --> 00:04:44,559
what do players think, did this match their expectations and.

76
00:04:45,145 --> 00:04:46,846
A lot of them was not what we wanted to hear.

77
00:04:46,846 --> 00:04:49,388
Like, oh, it felt like I was hanging with a foam bat.

78
00:04:49,388 --> 00:04:50,989
Is this a pool noodle?

79
00:04:50,989 --> 00:04:51,509
I don't know.

80
00:04:51,509 --> 00:04:57,212
But the worst case is it really harmed the character fantasy we were going for.

81
00:04:57,212 --> 00:05:01,374
We wanted them to feel like a samurai, and this was not honoring that.

82
00:05:01,374 --> 00:05:05,437
So what could we do to really make sure we honor that?

83
00:05:05,437 --> 00:05:08,578
A crisp idea, like what contract do we have with the player?

84
00:05:13,681 --> 00:05:16,783
This lethality contract, you know, what does it mean to be a samurai?

85
00:05:16,783 --> 00:05:21,627
And we talked about the standoffs being core to that feeling of the blade is sharp.

86
00:05:21,627 --> 00:05:23,508
How do we bring that to the rest of combat?

87
00:05:23,508 --> 00:05:26,931
As I was saying earlier, sword combat must be lethal.

88
00:05:26,931 --> 00:05:29,573
And there's other elements of combat, too.

89
00:05:29,573 --> 00:05:32,675
You know, when headshots and assassinations also had to kill

90
00:05:32,675 --> 00:05:35,157
and made sense to the players, like, oh, if I use an arrow

91
00:05:35,157 --> 00:05:37,159
and hit them in the head, they should die.

92
00:05:37,159 --> 00:05:41,102
We had to be a lot more cognizant of what it meant to players' expectations

93
00:05:41,102 --> 00:05:41,822
of this fantasy.

94
00:05:42,757 --> 00:05:46,438
And so we had to be a lot more harder on our limits of our HP,

95
00:05:46,438 --> 00:05:51,200
you know, number of hits to kill without upgrades had to be within a shorter band.

96
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:55,862
And even for our difficulty scaling, we can say, no, no, no, we need to keep it lower.

97
00:05:55,862 --> 00:05:58,704
We need to keep it so that doesn't inflate even on hard, et cetera.

98
00:05:58,704 --> 00:05:59,404
There are other ways to do this,

99
00:05:59,404 --> 00:06:02,325
which I'll talk about in a minute.

100
00:06:03,802 --> 00:06:05,144
And there's no RPG enemy levels.

101
00:06:05,144 --> 00:06:09,950
Part of this was HP inflation, but most of it was just harming the reality

102
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:14,376
of the game, like we've been we were presenting this as a grounded samurai game.

103
00:06:14,376 --> 00:06:15,758
Those RPG levels just didn't fit.

104
00:06:17,282 --> 00:06:18,502
And that sounds great.

105
00:06:18,502 --> 00:06:20,924
You know, OK, I'll just strip it all away. No problem. Right.

106
00:06:20,924 --> 00:06:24,225
Now, we need to have some way to provide challenge and escalation.

107
00:06:24,225 --> 00:06:26,767
Have your, you know, armor and swords feel meaningful.

108
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:29,868
If they didn't, you know, how do we how do we make sure the players

109
00:06:29,868 --> 00:06:32,670
keep engaged with, you know, reward loops or, you know,

110
00:06:32,670 --> 00:06:35,271
the combat loop that we're trying to provide?

111
00:06:35,271 --> 00:06:38,273
So, you know, we had to start reevaluating what we were doing and say,

112
00:06:38,273 --> 00:06:42,435
well, maybe we need to push on other angles, specifically

113
00:06:42,435 --> 00:06:45,377
talking about being more defensive for enemies to protect a low HP.

114
00:06:45,377 --> 00:06:46,738
We're pushing down the.

115
00:06:47,964 --> 00:06:52,286
number of hits to kill to like maybe four or five, maybe three in some cases.

116
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:55,649
But we need to have them to block and parry, you know, pretty standard stuff.

117
00:06:55,649 --> 00:06:58,851
But we just had we may have gone a little bit too far.

118
00:06:58,851 --> 00:07:01,933
We tried to say, OK, no, they have to be really on their toes

119
00:07:01,933 --> 00:07:04,014
and have them block and parry the hero.

120
00:07:04,014 --> 00:07:05,115
And they're like, oh, no, no, no, no.

121
00:07:05,115 --> 00:07:06,376
It just was too far.

122
00:07:06,376 --> 00:07:10,298
It was too, too frustrating for players.

123
00:07:10,298 --> 00:07:12,260
But at the same time, though, you know, like.

124
00:07:17,105 --> 00:07:22,018
them, but it became the predominant strategy. We needed to have a way to have the players

125
00:07:22,018 --> 00:07:26,008
break through those defenses and still feel like a samurai in an awesome way.

126
00:07:30,353 --> 00:07:33,435
So pushing on going on the offensive was a big part of this.

127
00:07:33,435 --> 00:07:36,396
Like, you know, we added a stagger meter, a pretty standard portion of melee

128
00:07:36,396 --> 00:07:38,137
combat games nowadays.

129
00:07:38,137 --> 00:07:40,258
But we try to do it in a little bit different of a way.

130
00:07:40,258 --> 00:07:42,659
Not all attacks did stagger damage.

131
00:07:42,659 --> 00:07:47,221
Light attacks were faster and heavy attacks did that stagger damage.

132
00:07:47,221 --> 00:07:49,022
But they also were the same amount.

133
00:07:49,022 --> 00:07:51,263
We didn't want one attack to be overly used to the other.

134
00:07:51,263 --> 00:07:53,904
We're like, oh, you only heavy attack because it just does more damage.

135
00:07:54,614 --> 00:08:00,304
And it also really pushed us for helping an enemy variety, like that heavy shield guy in the upper right,

136
00:08:00,304 --> 00:08:04,011
like he could slow you down so other enemies would come in, like that spear on the upper left.

137
00:08:05,042 --> 00:08:09,326
is a huge element of our encounter design and how we actually got an enemy variety.

138
00:08:09,326 --> 00:08:13,150
It's like a speed of stagger can change how you approach these enemies,

139
00:08:13,150 --> 00:08:15,152
especially with the speed of heavy attacks.

140
00:08:15,152 --> 00:08:18,475
But it also lets us start to expand what other things a player could do.

141
00:08:18,475 --> 00:08:23,159
And that led us to open the door to stances.

142
00:08:23,159 --> 00:08:27,603
If those who know how our stance system works, essentially you match.

143
00:08:28,164 --> 00:08:29,785
a stance to a specific enemy type.

144
00:08:29,785 --> 00:08:35,227
So that shieldman in the upper right, you use shield stance or water stance for our game.

145
00:08:35,227 --> 00:08:40,309
And it, you know, breaks through to the defenses faster, but not additional damage.

146
00:08:40,309 --> 00:08:45,692
As I said before, because speed of stagger was a huge element of our encounter composition and design,

147
00:08:45,692 --> 00:08:50,113
enemy aggression and how fast people attack, if you could break them faster, that was a huge deal.

148
00:08:51,151 --> 00:08:53,833
And to be clear, this is not a hard solve.

149
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:56,054
You know, unaligned attacks would get reversed or dodged,

150
00:08:56,054 --> 00:09:00,056
but it wasn't the only... you didn't have to do it.

151
00:09:00,056 --> 00:09:01,837
However, it was on Fantasy and on-brand.

152
00:09:01,837 --> 00:09:05,599
It felt really cool to break through an enemy's defense using the right stance.

153
00:09:05,599 --> 00:09:08,321
And it was definitely part of that Samurai Fantasy stances.

154
00:09:08,321 --> 00:09:10,662
But the reason not to make it a hard solve is...

155
00:09:12,745 --> 00:09:16,627
completely different order, they may not have the stance or they're like you know

156
00:09:16,627 --> 00:09:19,369
maybe they're not skilled enough, whatever it may be, it's okay not to

157
00:09:19,369 --> 00:09:22,471
require it. They could get around it and they still felt smart and like

158
00:09:22,471 --> 00:09:27,715
got around his defenses and still killed him. That being said, this is a great

159
00:09:27,715 --> 00:09:31,878
baseline. We had to go from, expand from here. We had to escalate challenge for

160
00:09:31,878 --> 00:09:34,139
the enemies. How are we gonna do that?

161
00:09:34,139 --> 00:09:34,399
Well

162
00:09:39,022 --> 00:09:41,904
A lot of it was actually mirroring, like mirroring the lethality of the hero,

163
00:09:41,904 --> 00:09:44,426
you know, less hits to kill to the other direction.

164
00:09:44,426 --> 00:09:46,328
Enemies have to start to be more lethal.

165
00:09:46,328 --> 00:09:49,930
And we had an injective variety, as I said earlier on the first slides.

166
00:09:49,930 --> 00:09:53,013
You know, weapon usage, as I just said, and counter composition

167
00:09:53,013 --> 00:09:55,695
played into that, that includes their aggression, their speed

168
00:09:55,695 --> 00:09:58,397
and what movesets have to challenge them with new types of attacks,

169
00:09:58,397 --> 00:10:01,039
including the unblockable and parable attacks.

170
00:10:01,039 --> 00:10:02,900
But also, of course, increased enemy damage.

171
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:06,603
That's that lethality I'm referring to where they push back on you.

172
00:10:08,907 --> 00:10:12,129
But at the same time, we still had to increase HP, but carefully.

173
00:10:12,129 --> 00:10:14,991
You know, we had to have sword upgrades feel meaningful.

174
00:10:14,991 --> 00:10:16,993
And a lot of that came down also to character art,

175
00:10:16,993 --> 00:10:19,895
where you could see the difference, like, oh, he's more armored.

176
00:10:19,895 --> 00:10:21,376
That justifies it some more.

177
00:10:21,376 --> 00:10:23,698
But that doesn't mean we went out of control like a huge amount.

178
00:10:23,698 --> 00:10:25,319
We had to really be mindful of this.

179
00:10:26,372 --> 00:10:31,400
So a good example of those, the worst case scenario is you can encounter the far right guy before any upgrades.

180
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:38,390
This is the worst case scenario. We still would have like maybe 10 to 12 hits to kill on that guy. That could be bad.

181
00:10:38,390 --> 00:10:41,455
But we had some other mechanisms in our world that actually really helped us out.

182
00:10:42,839 --> 00:10:47,402
So in our actual world, we actually broke it down into kind of like prefectures.

183
00:10:47,402 --> 00:10:49,824
Each area had a different tier of enemies.

184
00:10:49,824 --> 00:10:52,185
So you can see on this map here all the different colors.

185
00:10:52,185 --> 00:10:56,288
A little bit harder to look at a little bit, but the white areas are kind of like the intro

186
00:10:56,288 --> 00:11:01,411
enemies and then you have like the orange, blue, red and green as they escalate through the island.

187
00:11:01,411 --> 00:11:05,934
And so you start down here in the lower portion of the island and it's actually blocked off

188
00:11:05,934 --> 00:11:07,255
to the upper part.

189
00:11:07,255 --> 00:11:10,217
There's a choke point right at the start at the tip of the blue part of the south.

190
00:11:10,632 --> 00:11:15,354
And that actually helped us say you can't encounter the green guys at the top.

191
00:11:15,354 --> 00:11:19,355
You have to, you know, get past that story checkpoint. You have to get some upgrades.

192
00:11:19,355 --> 00:11:25,217
So that mitigated the upper band it could get up into, which is what we're really trying to avoid.

193
00:11:25,217 --> 00:11:28,378
And it also helped us a little bit with balance, trying to make sure that you didn't over level.

194
00:11:28,378 --> 00:11:32,500
I'll talk about that more. We didn't completely solve that, but it did help us kind of say,

195
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,540
oh yeah, this is as far as you could go for now.

196
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:34,580
So.

197
00:11:37,077 --> 00:11:40,762
With all that in mind, you know, like, what about, like, how do we present this information?

198
00:11:40,762 --> 00:11:43,967
How do we show number of hits to kill?

199
00:11:43,967 --> 00:11:45,489
Now, we showed this earlier with the UI.

200
00:11:45,489 --> 00:11:49,375
There's a lot of layers in the early, obviously, debugging versions of this,

201
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:50,497
but it actually just really...

202
00:11:53,982 --> 00:12:00,005
less being more. A big portion of our art direction was minimal UI.

203
00:12:00,005 --> 00:12:03,506
And also it was into our benefit, the comment and speed for Ghost is actually

204
00:12:03,506 --> 00:12:07,767
pretty fast and a lot can happen and all this UI flying everywhere actually made

205
00:12:07,767 --> 00:12:11,289
it harder. Good news we got rid of the armor points which are in some of these

206
00:12:11,289 --> 00:12:11,749
earlier ones.

207
00:12:12,289 --> 00:12:14,871
But we still need to show progress against other stuff.

208
00:12:14,871 --> 00:12:17,392
Like you can see the stagger bar, which is the purple in the upper left,

209
00:12:17,392 --> 00:12:19,593
got turned into this kind of arced bar.

210
00:12:19,593 --> 00:12:21,695
A little lighter weight, easier to see.

211
00:12:21,695 --> 00:12:23,135
We needed to show progress,

212
00:12:23,135 --> 00:12:25,017
but we also didn't really need to show hit points

213
00:12:25,017 --> 00:12:27,438
because those hits that killed were low.

214
00:12:27,438 --> 00:12:28,939
We have a low health indicator,

215
00:12:28,939 --> 00:12:31,680
but it was just there to say, oh, you're almost there.

216
00:12:31,680 --> 00:12:33,161
That was huge and important to us

217
00:12:33,161 --> 00:12:36,183
to make sure that you still had showed progress for that,

218
00:12:36,183 --> 00:12:38,004
but we didn't need to have all that information.

219
00:12:38,522 --> 00:12:44,987
And surprisingly, players were more accepting of slightly more hits with less information.

220
00:12:44,987 --> 00:12:48,890
It's for like the lower band. So if you're like five or six hits, you might not need to show

221
00:12:48,890 --> 00:12:53,634
anything. Of course, if you're higher, we might have to show something which I'll talk about in

222
00:12:53,634 --> 00:12:58,338
a bit. But essentially, we were kind of surprised that people were willing to accept more hits if

223
00:12:58,338 --> 00:13:01,480
there was less UI to show it, especially when it's lower hit points.

224
00:13:04,384 --> 00:13:08,847
So this kind of gets into this interesting question of design by feel or like how do we

225
00:13:08,847 --> 00:13:13,710
data use data to confirm it. Well we have the kind of standard hits to kill chart a lot of games have

