00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:17,753
where it's like oh yeah this is the number of hits to kill a target based on these progression

227
00:13:17,753 --> 00:13:23,717
values. We needed to kind of see what our design sense was and what expectations players had and

228
00:13:23,717 --> 00:13:28,260
it's like okay well this is six hits to kill if you have these upgrades how does that feel

229
00:13:28,260 --> 00:13:31,062
when we test that and so we kind of charted it all out.

230
00:13:31,495 --> 00:13:35,779
But it's also kind of interesting what the bans are, you know, we don't, players could, as I said

231
00:13:35,779 --> 00:13:40,823
before, go anywhere they want in an open world game. They could, you know, complete some content,

232
00:13:40,823 --> 00:13:45,727
not others. How do we make it sure what is the acceptable range, if you will, between value?

233
00:13:45,727 --> 00:13:50,331
Is it four to six hits at this point in the game? Do they have certain charms and upgrades?

234
00:13:50,331 --> 00:13:52,653
These are all questions we all factored into our sheets.

235
00:13:53,349 --> 00:13:57,314
including difficulty balancing, like to the hero, as I said earlier, for enemies,

236
00:13:57,314 --> 00:14:02,059
we increase damage on different difficulties, but we never increase their HP or their stagger values

237
00:14:02,059 --> 00:14:07,907
because stagger had similar implications to HP where if it was too high players would get frustrated

238
00:14:07,907 --> 00:14:09,669
and like, oh this guy just feels like a wall.

239
00:14:10,314 --> 00:14:11,775
But we can push all the other angles,

240
00:14:11,775 --> 00:14:14,358
so I said damage output, aggression,

241
00:14:14,358 --> 00:14:17,480
moveset timing for parry and dodge, huge part of that.

242
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:19,682
We charted those out in similar things

243
00:14:19,682 --> 00:14:21,043
where you number hits to kill the hero

244
00:14:21,043 --> 00:14:24,005
and matching those expectations for the higher difficulties.

245
00:14:24,005 --> 00:14:26,968
Talking about higher difficulties,

246
00:14:26,968 --> 00:14:30,491
we actually added another post-launch experiment

247
00:14:30,491 --> 00:14:32,953
initially called lethal difficulty.

248
00:14:32,953 --> 00:14:34,534
We really wanted to push something

249
00:14:34,534 --> 00:14:36,936
that was not just harder.

250
00:14:36,936 --> 00:14:39,798
It was something that felt maximally lethal.

251
00:14:41,878 --> 00:14:45,439
before of like, slash slash, someone's dead, or you could be dead instantly.

252
00:14:45,439 --> 00:14:50,280
It ended up being harder, and we, you know, we pushed a lot of the stuff to the extremes,

253
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:53,701
but you know, we actually increased the damage of the player to make sure that when you're

254
00:14:53,701 --> 00:14:59,683
taking so much, you can die in two hits, that they would also go down in one to two hits.

255
00:14:59,683 --> 00:15:00,823
That felt, felt right.

256
00:15:00,823 --> 00:15:04,484
We were trying to do something different, but it did narrow our progression band, and

257
00:15:04,484 --> 00:15:09,085
we're like, okay, we want to try this more kind of role-playing, more fantasy-fulfilling

258
00:15:09,085 --> 00:15:09,845
difficulty mode.

259
00:15:10,291 --> 00:15:15,073
But it's OK if that progression player doesn't feel as impactful necessarily,

260
00:15:15,073 --> 00:15:19,095
because this was actually more successful than we thought it was going to be.

261
00:15:19,095 --> 00:15:20,595
You know, it hit the fantasy the way you want to.

262
00:15:20,595 --> 00:15:22,756
It felt like this untapped potential.

263
00:15:22,756 --> 00:15:25,217
And people really started replaying portions of the content

264
00:15:25,217 --> 00:15:27,558
more than we expected in a really great way.

265
00:15:27,558 --> 00:15:30,180
And especially for the challenging encounters like our duels,

266
00:15:30,180 --> 00:15:34,041
people are like, I want a no hit run and I want to make sure that I do it perfectly.

267
00:15:34,041 --> 00:15:36,742
It was just so great to see the community engage with that

268
00:15:36,742 --> 00:15:39,163
and also be part of that, say, oh, yeah, this is what I expected.

269
00:15:41,183 --> 00:15:44,766
So with all those things in mind, like how do we confirm all those, you know,

270
00:15:44,766 --> 00:15:46,547
the difficulty modes, the hits to kill?

271
00:15:46,547 --> 00:15:50,731
How do we know we're in the right band, those ranges I talked about earlier?

272
00:15:50,731 --> 00:15:53,814
Well, we had to have certain player models and play testing, as I said before,

273
00:15:53,814 --> 00:15:57,757
I keep saying play testing all the time, because it's really important.

274
00:15:57,757 --> 00:15:58,017
But.

275
00:15:58,737 --> 00:16:04,178
It's, we needed to make sure that we hit those progression targets for each of the difficulties

276
00:16:04,178 --> 00:16:10,000
and those player types. So we had three player types. We had the linear, average, and wide players,

277
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:14,420
how they played the game. It's trying to match, you know, how much of the open world content that

278
00:16:14,420 --> 00:16:19,481
they had done. Linear is just going through the main story. Average is doing kind of a mixture

279
00:16:19,481 --> 00:16:22,842
of a little bit of content, some aside stuff, and wide goes as wide as possible.

280
00:16:26,318 --> 00:16:31,201
sword level, HP, like where they were when they did onsen, armor, etc.

281
00:16:31,201 --> 00:16:32,842
And see where they landed.

282
00:16:32,842 --> 00:16:36,504
And if that matched their expectation for that band of hits to kill.

283
00:16:36,504 --> 00:16:39,906
In the upper right you can see a chart of five players who finished the game

284
00:16:39,906 --> 00:16:41,627
and we can consider them the average band.

285
00:16:41,627 --> 00:16:44,309
And what's really great about looking at that and seeing where they were

286
00:16:44,309 --> 00:16:47,151
and how much content they had completed over time,

287
00:16:47,151 --> 00:16:48,692
we can ask them questions.

288
00:16:53,914 --> 00:16:56,995
but more like, oh yeah, did you feel like your upgrades mattered?

289
00:16:56,995 --> 00:17:00,396
Did you feel like you were fulfilling the samurai fantasy in this way?

290
00:17:00,396 --> 00:17:02,636
Did you feel kind of like that journey?

291
00:17:02,636 --> 00:17:05,957
Which is really great because we target this specifically.

292
00:17:05,957 --> 00:17:10,198
But there are parts where we had to bend the rules, you know, like not

293
00:17:10,198 --> 00:17:12,799
this is not a one size fits all solution, you know,

294
00:17:12,799 --> 00:17:15,580
maybe painfully obvious to you, but duels are boss fights.

295
00:17:15,580 --> 00:17:17,940
And we thought, oh, we can apply the same kind of lethality

296
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,921
feeling to this experience. But.

297
00:17:20,389 --> 00:17:23,873
You know, if it's over in seconds, you know, that's not what players wanted.

298
00:17:23,873 --> 00:17:27,136
You know, we we are heavily inspired by Samurai films.

299
00:17:27,136 --> 00:17:32,281
But even though those battles over in seconds, it didn't exactly match that.

300
00:17:32,281 --> 00:17:34,684
So what players wanted was like a skill challenge.

301
00:17:34,684 --> 00:17:36,225
They wanted a longer fight.

302
00:17:36,383 --> 00:17:40,328
more defensive, more agile, and they wanted to make sure that it felt like it was a longer,

303
00:17:40,328 --> 00:17:45,895
you know, longer experience. And kind of the same as Samurai Cinema, it's kind of a reversal of

304
00:17:45,895 --> 00:17:52,323
expectations. So we kind of had to flip it around and say, okay, hits to kill have to be higher,

305
00:17:52,323 --> 00:17:56,107
we have to add a health bar back, which actually kind of helped because it made it feel more like

306
00:17:56,672 --> 00:17:59,534
an epic boss fight, which is the point.

307
00:17:59,534 --> 00:18:02,375
And we had it kind of subdivided a little bit with, you know,

308
00:18:02,375 --> 00:18:04,156
Clash of the Sword to say, okay, this is not too long.

309
00:18:04,156 --> 00:18:06,718
Yeah, this is a lot more hits, but, you know,

310
00:18:06,718 --> 00:18:08,359
each section feels appropriately length.

311
00:18:08,359 --> 00:18:10,980
So kind of like players are like, okay, this doesn't feel like a slog.

312
00:18:10,980 --> 00:18:16,103
So it was an interesting thing because we had to add the health bar,

313
00:18:16,103 --> 00:18:17,504
not just because it feels epic,

314
00:18:17,504 --> 00:18:19,024
but to understand when it hits a killer higher,

315
00:18:19,024 --> 00:18:22,406
we had to add a health bar to say, oh, am I making progress?

316
00:18:22,406 --> 00:18:24,808
As I said before in the UI slide,

317
00:18:24,808 --> 00:18:26,448
we condensed it down to like, you know, maybe.

318
00:18:29,725 --> 00:18:32,107
In this case, players wanted to know how far they were doing,

319
00:18:32,107 --> 00:18:35,110
how they're doing, it's long enough.

320
00:18:35,110 --> 00:18:36,592
However, you know, still there were some issues

321
00:18:36,592 --> 00:18:38,093
with feeling too short or too long,

322
00:18:38,093 --> 00:18:39,875
and we iterate a lot on this in development

323
00:18:39,875 --> 00:18:42,857
if we get the right feeling for our duels.

324
00:18:42,857 --> 00:18:44,679
Another element of where we had to bend the rules

325
00:18:44,679 --> 00:18:46,320
was our multiplayer mode.

326
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:52,926
So Legends mode is a two to four player co-op experience.

327
00:18:53,541 --> 00:18:57,604
And there's a lot of realities in multiplayer that we kind of had to kind of accept.

328
00:18:57,604 --> 00:19:00,846
And that is four versus one or even two versus one target.

329
00:19:00,846 --> 00:19:02,186
Enemies go down fast.

330
00:19:02,186 --> 00:19:06,749
And if HP is too low, it's going to be like they can't get any attacks out.

331
00:19:06,749 --> 00:19:10,892
They don't. That's the go to solution for everything.

332
00:19:10,892 --> 00:19:11,912
It's not what we were.

333
00:19:11,912 --> 00:19:14,934
We couldn't really do the same thing as before, especially too,

334
00:19:14,934 --> 00:19:17,676
because we also had more of a gear scaling, kind of like power scaling,

335
00:19:17,676 --> 00:19:20,237
gear power calculation that would scale a little bit

336
00:19:20,237 --> 00:19:21,738
between incoming and outcoming damage.

337
00:19:22,327 --> 00:19:25,730
Plus, some of the player abilities are more magical in nature and like, you know, big

338
00:19:25,730 --> 00:19:27,512
area of effect attacks and damage.

339
00:19:27,512 --> 00:19:30,795
We couldn't just do the same thing as before.

340
00:19:30,795 --> 00:19:35,500
It gets even more applicable because supernatural enemies were a big part of this, you know,

341
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:35,700
the Oni.

342
00:19:36,718 --> 00:19:40,600
And as a result, it was a situation where it felt like they're mini bosses

343
00:19:40,600 --> 00:19:44,501
and they had their own abilities and magic and buffs like healing nearby enemies

344
00:19:44,501 --> 00:19:48,323
or, you know, regenerating or whatever it may be.

345
00:19:48,323 --> 00:19:50,824
And it was a situation where like, OK, we need a way to show this to the player.

346
00:19:50,824 --> 00:19:53,885
We had to show UI again, especially because, as I said,

347
00:19:53,885 --> 00:19:56,506
on the duel slide, the hits to kill is much higher.

348
00:19:56,506 --> 00:19:58,207
We had to show that progress.

349
00:19:58,207 --> 00:20:01,228
And it just it was a completely different expectation for our players.

350
00:20:01,756 --> 00:20:05,577
And as I said before, especially with these Oni enemies,

351
00:20:05,577 --> 00:20:11,318
we wanted them to live longer and be more of a threat to players.

352
00:20:11,318 --> 00:20:13,318
So, some final problems.

353
00:20:13,318 --> 00:20:15,799
This was a great push for us towards Samurai Fantasy,

354
00:20:15,799 --> 00:20:18,440
but there were some issues we ran into.

355
00:20:18,440 --> 00:20:20,420
One of them was over-leveling.

356
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:22,140
So, as I said before, the wide player,

357
00:20:22,140 --> 00:20:25,021
the person we did it for our player models,

358
00:20:25,021 --> 00:20:27,662
they went wider than expected in our...

359
00:20:29,035 --> 00:20:30,595
never really mirrored the same thing.

360
00:20:30,595 --> 00:20:32,195
So you could do almost all the content

361
00:20:32,195 --> 00:20:34,476
in this lower portion of Tsushima, which is Zuhara,

362
00:20:34,476 --> 00:20:36,636
they would do almost all of it.

363
00:20:36,636 --> 00:20:39,317
And then they would just start steamrolling their way

364
00:20:39,317 --> 00:20:41,157
through the rest of the content.

365
00:20:41,157 --> 00:20:42,858
Well, part of this was actually acceptable for us

366
00:20:42,858 --> 00:20:46,398
on the player journey, where, oh, I'm becoming the ghost,

367
00:20:46,398 --> 00:20:49,239
I have new weapons, new ways to defeat enemies.

368
00:20:49,239 --> 00:20:49,919
And it's like, okay,

369
00:20:49,919 --> 00:20:51,620
it's okay to be a little bit overpowered.

370
00:20:51,620 --> 00:20:53,600
Not perfect, there's a place

371
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:54,860
we could have done balancing here.

372
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:56,981
We tried to use that choke point, as I mentioned earlier,

373
00:20:56,981 --> 00:20:58,061
to kind of like hit a cap.

374
00:20:58,602 --> 00:21:02,042
But definitely we're like, OK, we thought we had a correct range,

375
00:21:02,042 --> 00:21:05,363
but we were a little bit off there. Definitely a place to improve for.

376
00:21:05,363 --> 00:21:07,104
Another part of this is damage reactions.

377
00:21:07,104 --> 00:21:10,765
We talked a little bit about this in the armor point slide.

378
00:21:10,765 --> 00:21:13,045
I know it was kind of confusing whether you're doing damage or not.

379
00:21:13,045 --> 00:21:16,766
This still applied in places for us, like when you have sparks versus blood,

380
00:21:16,766 --> 00:21:20,247
is what we said a lot like, oh, if blood comes out, they're taking damage.

381
00:21:20,247 --> 00:21:23,248
Especially like we have a similar stuff from like

382
00:21:23,248 --> 00:21:24,708
to find a game terminology like super armor.

383
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:26,788
Those will show sparks because they.

384
00:21:26,896 --> 00:21:28,937
they're not being interrupted and they're going to come on through.

385
00:21:28,937 --> 00:21:32,399
But sometimes players would have a hard time reading that,

386
00:21:32,399 --> 00:21:34,860
especially because their combat speed was very fast.

387
00:21:34,860 --> 00:21:38,722
That kind of combat feedback, even with sound effects and haptics and so forth,

388
00:21:38,722 --> 00:21:41,023
we didn't quite nail that feeling.

389
00:21:41,023 --> 00:21:45,846
It was not exactly what, you know, we didn't get a nail on a knockout out of the park.

390
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:49,648
But, as I said before, way bigger improvement over our previous iterations

391
00:21:49,648 --> 00:21:52,309
on giving feedback to the player on damage reactions,

392
00:21:52,309 --> 00:21:53,870
but definitely room for improvement.

393
00:21:56,465 --> 00:22:01,026
So last thoughts and takeaways just for us and when working through this problem,

394
00:22:01,026 --> 00:22:04,587
you know, core design decisions and tuning should really be as much as possible

395
00:22:04,587 --> 00:22:07,468
support the character fantasy core system and core combat.

396
00:22:07,468 --> 00:22:10,429
Stuff like this has a huge impact on the play experience

397
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:12,150
and making sure that you can target say, oh, no, no, no,

398
00:22:12,150 --> 00:22:14,150
we don't want to ruin that or undermine it.

399
00:22:14,150 --> 00:22:17,351
It's easy to get caught into the swirl saying, oh, this system will help here.

400
00:22:17,351 --> 00:22:20,112
Or in my or another game, just like similar,

401
00:22:20,112 --> 00:22:22,433
we might have to go back to the drawing board a little bit.

402
00:22:22,974 --> 00:22:27,219
especially for us, I'm talking about for lethality, you know, that goes both ways,

403
00:22:27,219 --> 00:22:31,425
that, you know, there's an expectation for that, and there's a lot of learnings for us on that angle.

404
00:22:32,759 --> 00:22:36,442
And that enemy defensive behavior is critical, like the stagger, the blocking, the dodging.

405
00:22:36,442 --> 00:22:40,025
You know, these are these are core combat mechanics are in a lot of games, too,

406
00:22:40,025 --> 00:22:42,627
but really emphasizing that, especially for protecting low HP.

407
00:22:42,627 --> 00:22:46,250
But in turn, of course, making sure player verbs and player attacks

408
00:22:46,250 --> 00:22:49,392
and actions can counter and counter that gameplay.

409
00:22:49,392 --> 00:22:51,714
You know, stances for us was a big part of that.

410
00:22:51,714 --> 00:22:56,058
Make sure that was a solid part of the character fantasy, as I mentioned a second ago.

411
00:22:56,058 --> 00:22:59,720
And trust your design intuition on what does it feel like?

412
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:01,862
This is a lot of portions of this are designed by feel.

413
00:23:02,525 --> 00:23:08,170
And it's important to make sure that you understand that,

414
00:23:08,170 --> 00:23:11,974
hey, this isn't like a perfect number that I need to get a

415
00:23:11,974 --> 00:23:15,177
certain sense of how it's going to be. But of course, you got to

416
00:23:15,177 --> 00:23:17,879
verify with playtesting. It's always good to playtest as much

417
00:23:17,879 --> 00:23:20,622
as possible and verify without your own confirmation bias of

418
00:23:20,622 --> 00:23:23,524
how you play it yourself a million times, which you should.

419
00:23:23,524 --> 00:23:28,288
Difficulty balancing escalation and progression should not

420
00:23:29,208 --> 00:23:34,071
require major HP inflation. It would be best to make sure you try to avoid it,

421
00:23:34,071 --> 00:23:38,335
especially for, in our case, this character fantasy.

422
00:23:38,335 --> 00:23:41,437
And a huge element is just making sure to push all the other knobs you've got.

423
00:23:41,437 --> 00:23:47,261
Aggression, moveset, timing, damage output, all these are really, really, really core.

424
00:23:47,261 --> 00:23:51,344
But if you're going to increase HP, which we had to as well,

425
00:23:51,344 --> 00:23:54,867
do it carefully. Do it thoughtfully and with intention.

426
00:23:55,682 --> 00:23:58,242
It is okay to do so like we did before with character art,

427
00:23:58,242 --> 00:24:01,443
whether it be in our Legends mode or whatever it may be.

428
00:24:01,443 --> 00:24:04,284
Those are all important elements to consider,

429
00:24:04,284 --> 00:24:06,064
but do it in a way that you're mindful about it.

430
00:24:06,064 --> 00:24:08,785
So I really hope you enjoyed our kind of a quick look

431
00:24:08,785 --> 00:24:10,765
at how we tackle lethality within Ghost of Tsushima

432
00:24:10,765 --> 00:24:13,606
and its impact on combat balance.

433
00:24:13,606 --> 00:24:15,546
It was a rollercoaster and a ride,

434
00:24:15,546 --> 00:24:18,867
but we felt like we hit land on a pretty good solution.

435
00:24:18,867 --> 00:24:21,548
If you want to know more information at GDC 2021

436
00:24:21,548 --> 00:24:24,328
about Ghost of Tsushima specifically,

437
00:24:24,488 --> 00:24:29,432
There's another combat talk here at GDC from our studio head, Chris Zimmerman.

438
00:24:29,432 --> 00:24:34,416
He goes into more of the depth about the mechanics of combat, more like how we built them exactly

439
00:24:34,416 --> 00:24:37,959
and through the years of trying to work on this game.

440
00:24:37,959 --> 00:24:40,560
And if you're interested in that, just make sure you check it out.

441
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:42,002
And yeah, it's a great talk.

